About
=====
Astrid is minimalistic content integration server. It tracks Git repositories
can run build tasks on them and expose the built repositories on the web. It's
important that Astrid separate to isolate its users' access rights.

Installation
============

Quickest way is to install Astrid from Python egg (run `python setup.py
bdist_egg` to build the egg) on the destination machine.

After egg installation, copy configuration files located in 'config' directory
into '~/.astrid' and strip the '.sample' extension.

Eventually edit the settings for your site.

